HEADWORD: Roebuck
<hw>Roe"buck`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st <ets>roe</ets>
+ <ets>buck</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small European and
Asiatic deer (<spn>Capreolus capraea</spn>) having erect, cylindrical,
branched antlers, forked at the summit. This, the smallest European
deer, is very nimble and graceful. It always prefers a mountainous
country, or high grounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roe, Richard</ent>⟦br⟧
